Lesson 4

#1) Choose a framework. This will give you a css style sheet that you can use! Sites with frameworks:

	Bootstrap: http://getbootstrap.com/ 
	Foundation: http://foundation.zurb.com/ 
	Yaml: http://www.yaml.de/ 
	960 Grid: http://960.gs/ 
	Susy: http://susy.oddbird.net/ 

#2) Include your own syle.css stylesheet to your /css file!

#3) Some code you may want to include in beginning.

	<!DOCTYPE html>
	<html lang=“en”>
	  <head>
	    <meta charset=“utf-8”>      <-- Uses characters you tell it to use
	    <meta http-equiv=“X-UA-Compatible” content=“IE=edge”>      <-- Gives internet explorer users best experience possible
 	    <meta name=“viewport” content=“width=device-width, initial-scale=1”>          <-- responsive text (good for use on mobile)
	    <title>Puppy Portfolio</title>
	    <link rel=“stylesheet” href=“css/bootstrap.css”>
	  </head/>
	  <body>
	    <div class=“container”>      <-- Put everything in bootstrap’s container
	      <div class="row">
	        <div class="col-md-6">
	          <img src="images/logo.png" alt="Udacity logo">
	        </div>
	        <div class="col-md-6 text-right text-uppercase"></div>
	          <h1>Jane Doette</h1>
	          <h4>Front-end Ninja</h4>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	    <div class="row">
	      <div class="col-md-12">
	        <hr>
	      </div>
	      <div class="row">
	        <div class"col-md-12">
	          <img class="img-responsive" src="images/puppy1.jpg" alt="Main puppy image!">
	        </div>
	      </div>
	      <div class="row">
	        <div class="col-md-12">
	          <h2>Featured Work</h2>
	        </div>
	      </div>
	      <div class="row">
	        <div class="col-md-4">
	          <img class="img-responsive" src="images/puppy2.jpg" alt="Appify puppy">
	          <h3 class="text-uppercase">Appify</h3>
	          <p>https://github.com/udacity/appify</p>
	        </div>
	      </div>
